{
  "stem": "12768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We thought that we were going to be greeted by Germans' guns coming across the strait.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And so we were all in-- in full gear, lying on the bottom of the-- on the decks, you know, with our guns ready and all, ready to go aboard to Denmark.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And instead, we were shouted, welcome home, about the 10,000 people in the city of Elsinore.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "It was such a beautiful sight that you can't-- we have the Hamlet castle on the right and the-- the beaches on the left, you know, and here sits the harbor.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And here was red and white flags put up, you know, and people were-- just started shouting, welcome home.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But of course, as a military unit, you can't always do-- so we got flowers, and then we start marching from Elsinore into Copenhagen.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And then we were going to overnight at schools around the city.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And the school that we came to was called [?",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "Husome ?] Street School.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 18,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "I just took a picture here, when I were in Denmark my last time on the 5th of May.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, it's funny to see the school again, the backyard where we were lying in and had our open fights with the Germans.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We lost three soldiers, because the still Danish quislings and the Danish Nazis were attacking us, you know?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And of course, we blew them out of the sky.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But we lost three.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "But we were sent the next day.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were already sent to-- down to the border of Denmark and Germany to take over the border guarding.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there we met the British unit which had been fighting before and started a war in Tobruk.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So it was a-- an old unit, you know, of British soldiers.",
      "word_count": 12
    }
  ],
